<HEAD>Photo Developer Who Blew Whistle On Dirty Pictures Fired</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Note contents of 7th graf</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A commercial photo lab processor who told police
about lewd photographs involving a man and a young girl says he was
fired for ``doing the right thing.''
   Charles Markey's action led to the arrest of William Bennett,
52, and Veronica Martinez, 45, who were charged with first-degree
sexual abuse, authorities said.
   Markey, 21, said he lost his job at Hot Shots 30 Minute Photo
Lab within minutes of the couple's arrest on Thursday.
   ``The arrest and his firing are totally unrelated,'' said a
manager at the lab, who identified himself only as Alan.
   Markey admitted he was 15 minutes late for work the day of the
arrests. But he also said his bosses had scolded him for calling
police and that ``everyone there gave me the silent treatment.''
   ``It seems silly, but they fired me for doing the right thing,''
he said.
   On Monday, he said, he found five photographs allegedly showing
Bennett, the owner of a music school, masturbating while a young
girl sat next to him on a piano bench.
   Markey tried to call his boss, he said, and when he couldn't
reach him, called the police.
