<1ST_LINE>r i AM-SAfrica-CasinoBlast     08-06 0128</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-SAfrica-Casino Blast,0131</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bomb Explodes In Casino, No Injuries</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bomb exploded in a hotel
casino moments after security officers discovered it and evacuated
the building, authorities said Saturday.
   Police said the bomb caused no damage because a special blanket
was thrown on it just before the blast. There were no injuries.
   The incident occurred Friday night at the Morula Sun, a resort
hotel near Pretoria in the black homeland of Bophuthatswana.
Gambling is illegal in South Africa, except in the homelands.
   No one claimed responsibility for setting the bomb.
   Police have blamed a recent series of explosions on the African
National Congress, the outlawed guerrilla movement which since 1961
has waged a violent campaign aimed at toppling South Africa's
white-led government.
</TEXT>
