<1ST_LINE>r i AM-China-Flood     08-06 0152</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-China-Flood,0157</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Flooding Kills At Least 21 In North China</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Torrential rains flooded 40 villages in north
China and killed at least 21 people, the official Xinhua News
Agency said Saturday.
   Xinhua's brief report said 19 other people were missing
following a 3{-hour deluge Saturday morning in Fenyang County in
Shanxi province.
   About 30,000 people were marooned by the flood waters, and at
least 100 houses were destroyed, it said.
   No details were given on rescue efforts in the latest of a
series of natural disasters to hit China this year.
   Most recent official figures on flash flooding a week ago in
coastal Zhejiang province put the death toll at 256, with 316
people missing.
   More than 500 other people have died throughout China in
separate floods, hailstorms and a typhoon this year, while a heat
wave in June and July claimed nearly 500 lives in central cities.
</TEXT>
